unittitle.value: New York University Library Accession Books

abstract.value: The collection contains ledgers recording the accession of books, periodicals, manuscripts, and other items by various New York University libraries between 1830 and 1967. Some ledgers contain catalogs of authors, theses, and bill payments.

p.value: Published citations should take the following form: Identification of item, date (if known); New York University Library Accession Books; MC 258; box number; folder number (if included); New York University Archives, New York University Libraries.
Materials found in collection; there is no documentation concerning the provenance of these materials.

The collection contains ledgers recording the accession of books, periodicals, manuscripts, and other items by various New York University libraries between 1830 and 1967. Some ledgers contain catalogs of authors, theses, and bill payments.
